Cyril Ramaphosa says the ANC needs to regroup as it's concerning that people are protesting against the party. JOHANNESBURG - Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa says it s time for the African National Congress (ANC) to rebuild itself and win back the confidence of the people. Ramaphosa has been on a two-day campaign in the dissolved municipality of Nqutu in KwaZulu-Natal this weekend.He says the ANC needs to regroup as it's concerning that people are protesting against the party. ANC is a hope merchant; it brings hope to our people and our people should never feel hopeless. Ramaphosa also flew to Newcastle where he addressed a number of members, including former provincial leaders, who are seen to oppose the president.